# Files the Tauri CLI's file-watcher ignores during `tauri dev`.
#
# IMPORTANT: this file controls dev-mode reload behavior, NOT bundling.
# Bundling in Tauri 2 is opt-IN via `tauri.conf.json -> bundle.resources`,
# so anything not listed there is already excluded from shipped binaries.
# `.tauriignore` exists here for two reasons:
#
#  1. Faster dev iterations — touching qa/ scenarios or fixtures shouldn't
#     trigger a Tauri rebuild. Without this, editing a markdown scenario
#     was triggering a full incremental recompile.
#  2. Documents intent — readers can see at a glance which trees are
#     dev-only and must never reach a user.

# Internal QA harness — scenarios, fixtures, WebDriver runner.
# Lives outside src/ and src-tauri/src/, never reaches the bundle.
/qa/

# Rust integration tests — compiled only by `cargo test`, never by
# `cargo build` / `tauri build`. Listed defensively.
/src-tauri/tests/

# Build outputs that the watcher would otherwise chase its own tail on.
/dist/
/src-tauri/target/

# Documentation that isn't shipped.
/CHANGELOG.md
/README.md
/docs/

# Working files / OS junk.
/.git/
/node_modules/
*.log
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
